</div>

<h3>Login Options</h3>
<ul>
<li>Email and Password</li>
<li>Google Sign-In (optional)</li>
</ul>

<h2>10. Key Rules to Remember</h2>

<div class="important">
<ol>
<li><strong>Revenue is NOT from Facebook</strong> - It comes from our database (Data Management section or webhooks)</li>
<li><strong>Leads are NOT from Facebook</strong> - They come from our database</li>
<li><strong>ROAS = Revenue ÷ Spend</strong> - Uses local revenue and Facebook spend</li>
<li><strong>If no revenue data exists, show 0</strong> - Don't try to fetch from Facebook</li>
<li><strong>Manual Refresh reads from database</strong> - It does NOT call Facebook API</li>
</ol>
</div>

<h2>11. Summary</h2>

<p>The Facebook Ads Dashboard is a tool to:</p>
<ol>
<li>View Facebook ad performance (spend, clicks, reach) synced from Facebook</li>
<li>Track revenue and leads from our own data sources</li>
<li>Calculate ROAS by combining both data sources</li>
<li>Get alerts when performance is bad or good</li>
<li>Manage multiple Pabbly ad accounts from one place</li>
</ol>

